Doppler ultrasound in diagnosis of liver tumor and portal hypertension. Technical aspects (equipment, presetting, enhancement) are considered together with new approaches like interventional radiology and Doppler ultrasound. In liver tumors Doppler US not always shows typical patterns: in hemangioma there is usually poor vascularization, while in malignant tumors the data are: high speed arterial blood flow turbulent flow in the feeding artery